<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Montenegrin Prime Minister: "Milosevic should reinstate the election results!"</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
used without permission, for "fair use" only<hr>

<FONT SIZE="+1">

<h1>Best Solution: Reinstate Election Results</h1>
                
<strong><em>BETA news agency</em></strong><P>

<h2>Nasa Borba, Beograd, FR Yugoslavia, 12/17 1996</h2>

<strong>Podgorica</strong>, Beta - Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Dukanovic
stated that the best solution for the current crisis in Serbia is to reinstate
the results from the second round of recent local elections.  In 
an interview for the daily <em>Vesti</em>, which is published in Serbian in
Frankfurt, Germany, Dukanovic said that even to him, let alone to foreign
governments and public opinion, "the explanation that the opposition has
rigged the elections which were, as everywhere else, organized by the 
authorities, sounds very unconvincing".  According the Podgorica daily 
<em>Pobjeda</em>, he emphasized that the reinstatement of the
election results would be "the best solution" for the current crisis in 
Serbia.<P>

Dukanovic emphasized that "the authorities in Serbia shouldn't be afraid to
do that; it is not a tragedy to loose power in several cities, even the
largest ones, if one has firm control of the republic and Federation".<P>

Montenegrin Prime Minister said that if it has become impossible to reinstate
the results because of the legal procedure, president Milosevic should 
"annul these and declare new local elections as soon as possible; this way
we are simply wasting time".<P>

According to Dukanovic, the solution for the crisis in Serbia is a condition
for improved relations with the international community: "everyone must
realize that huge internal, economic and social problems cannot be solved
without improved relations with the international community".  Dukanovic
concluded the interview by saying that the annulment of the second round
of local elections in Serbia has resulted in "irreparable damage both on
the internal and external plane".<P>

<hr>

Translated on 12/18/96<P>

<hr>
</FONT>
<A HREF="/info/students/marko/yuindpress.html"><IMG SRC="/info/students/marko
/pictures/home.gif" ALT="HOME" WIDTH=80 HIGHT=40></a>
