ARKZIN_ZG@ZAMIR-ZG.ZTN.APC.ORG (ARKzin Zagreb) ARKzin<P> 


<CENTER>
<h1>ARKzin - INDEX OF THE ISSUE 60 - 15. 3. 1996.</h1></CENTER>

<strong>HEADLINES:</strong><P>

<center><FONT SIZE="+2">
<a HREF="#tudjman">USA WARNS TUDJMAN: "WE KNOW WHAT YOU DO !"</a><P>
"Butcher's apprentice" is vigilantly watched in his endeavours to create his
master-piece: ethnically cleansed, one-party corporative state.<P>

<a HREF="#nationalism">NATIONALISM IN THE BALKANS IS NOT IMMANENT, BUT THE RESULT OF SLY POLITICAL MANIPULATION</a><P>
French professor has developed new and original view of the post-Yugoslav
problems.(pages 4/6)<P>

<a HREF="#ombudsman">THE INVISIBLE OMBUDSMAN !</a><P>
He has hidden himself, although his duty was to prevent the human rights
violations that have occured in Croatia on a large scale.(see page 8)<P>

<a HREF="#hdz">HDZ LEGALIZES VIOLATION OF HUMAN RIGHTS !!!</a><P>
The Allmighty Government, proposing the scandalous laws, will put artists,
scientists, Universities, NGO's under its control.(read Mato Vilac, page 16)<P>

<a HREF="#body">BODY ART IN ZAGREB !</a><P>
An artistic project of Marcel Li Antunez Roca to rebuild a new body in the
world of technology. (read: Epizoo- pages: 26/27)<P></FONT></center>
<hr>
<a NAME="tudjman">page: 2/3 CROATIAN GOVERNMENT TOLERATES CRIMES!(Hrvatska vlada tolerira zlocine!)</a><P>
author: ARKZIN'S INVESTIGATION TEAM<P>

In spite of increasing positive relation between Croatia and United States,
which is only on the basis of pragmatic, strategic interests, from the last
State Departement's Report on the state of human rights in Croatia, it is
obvious that America knows everything what happens here.
The report emphasizes crimes and ethnic cleansing in Krajina, noticing that
Croatia wants to legalize changes in population, caused by the military action,
than to render possible the return of Serb refugees and exiles.
The security forces have participated, or ignored, in numerous maltreatements
on the liberated territories. According to UNCRO there were about three to
five hundred  very brutal murders on the ethnical basis, than; plundering and
burning the houses, confinement and torturing of prisoners, depriving them of
just legal process. Many of Serbs have been tried in two @^s, on the charge of
mutiny, with no possibility to contact the lawyer. Judges were appointed on
the political and not on the competence and quality basis. Government didn't
establish the Temporary court for human rights although it's Constitutional
obligation, and didn't take a step to punish the perpetrators of those crimes.
Serbs in cities and towns are furhter exposed to the terror and menace and
forced to emigrate. Government also threatens to the liberty of press and
media. National TV (HTV), radio and most of the press are under total control.
Government also does't grant citizenship to Muslims in Croatia although they
comply with the conditions for it.<P>

<a NAME="nationalism">page: 4/6- THE END OF A DREAM OF ETHNICAL CLEANNESS (Kraj sna o etnickoj cistoci)</a><P>

author: DEJAN JOVIC<P>

"Serbian and Croatian identities are not clearly distinguished. Croatian
dialects are very often more different from each other than from Serb's
dialects of the same areas. Serbs are mostly atheists, but they base their
nationality on the orhtodox christianity, which they share with Russians,
Greeks, Roumanians, Bulgarians, Ukrainians, etc. Therefore it is not more
natural to build a Croatian or Serbian state than to build a Bosnian or
Yugoslav one. Nationalism was produced by the political elites, as an easiest
attempt to legitimate their new reign, which rests upon a permanent production
of fear and insecurity in the population. Hence the nationalism is not
congenital to Serbs, Croats, Muslims, but the result of systematical
manipulation."- says Catherine Samary, the university professor on the
"L'Universite: Paris IX - Dauphine", and author of the book:"Dissected
Yugoslavia", in her Arkzin's interview, and continues: "In Bosnia so many
atrocities have been committed to prove that it's "natural" for three nations
not to live together in one state.<P>
Usually "natural" means spontaneous and effortless, and no force is contained
in it.
The war was created out of a deep economic and social crises of the former
Yugoslavia, in which the republics elites have started to compete like the
companies on the market. Mrs. Samary differentiates two sorts of nationalism:
the agressive nationalism of big nations: Serbian Croatian Slovenian, and
pacifist  nationalism of small nations: Macedonians, Bosniacs who were even
not interested in dismemeberment of Yugoslav federacy where their nationalities
have been for the first time politicaly and culturaly recognized.
Tito's self-management principle, republicanism and federalism, the
industrialization of country, and uprooting of illiteracy, unfortunately have
been spoiled by the bolshevist one-partysm, and uncompromising beating off the
significant political differencies.
Ante Markovi 's liberal endeavour to save Yugoslavia has neglected the
collective entities, because liberal competition brings out the dominance of
stronger and richer, or dominance of one collective over other brought out by
majorization.
Mrs. Samary sees no the essential conflict in between Croatia and Serbia, but
between Serbia and Bosnia and Croatia and Bosnia. Dayton's peace agreement has
given Tudjman and Milosevic a free play in their tendencies to suppress the
opposition and independent media. The case of Studio B in Belgrade, the
Tudjman's "mayor affaire", the resignation of multiethnically orientated prime
minister Silajdzic are the first results of such "pragmatical" support of the
international community to the Balkans authoritarian chieftains.
The events in ex-Yugoslavia regrettably have reflected on Europe. The
pro-fascist and racist forces have raised up their heads against the
globalisation and multiculturalisation. They all demand from their nations to
be; outwardly imperialistic, on the frontiers protectionistic and inwardly
ethnically clean.
For Mrs. Samary, Bosnia is a turning point. If the multiethnic principle
prevails, the state will be re-established, and Balkan chieftains will finish
in Haag. If opposite, they will be rewarded and a hard time for the democracy
in Europe will continue.<P>

page: 7 - CROATIAN GOD MARS (Hrvatski Bog Mars)<P>
author: BOZO MATIC<P>

A strong authoritarianism of Croatian national mentality doesn't tolerate any
autonomous initiative. Everybody looks to  president Tudjman, what he will
say...
And president Tudjman, as usually, will manipulate with people, for his own
benefit and the benefit of his oligarchy, giving away crumbles here and there
to sooth the discontent of the war veterans, taxi drivers, retired people. On
the other side: Tudjman threatens workers with the police repression, in the
case of strikes and demonstration. As if workers, industry, transport, public
services, haven't contributed to the defense of the country.
Tudjman despises intellectuals, political parties, free-thinkers.
Tudjman knows nothing about economy, since he is surrounded by flunkeys and
their Potemkin's villages, the mirage of Croatian "economic miracle".
As a dictator he doesn't use an open crude violence of police and army, but
rather creates stupid laws, using HDZ majority machine in parliament.<P>

<a NAME="ombudsman">page: 8 -  BABAC'S  PASSION (Muke po Babcu)</a><P>
author: VERONIKA RESKOVIC<P>

Mr. Branko Babac the Croatian Public Legal Officer (Ombudsman) in his human
rights report to the parliament,made in february 1996. for the year 1994. has
told a rosy fairy tale about peaceful even boring country that functions like a
Suiss watch, which citizens are overcontented with all the institutions of a
system wide opened on their disposal.
Mr. Babac was hidden and self-abnegating for almost three years since his
appointement by the Croatian ~}ltitude of citizens, in searching for their
constitutional and legal rights, passes by his office, ignorant of his
existence.
The year 1994. was very prominent in human rights violation in Croatia, for
there were so many brutal evictions from flats, problems of refusals to grant
the Croatian citizenship, illegal firing from the job, blasting of houses,
dissapearance of people, illegal mobilizations...
One can read NGO's reports of that time or report of the Council of Europe,
State Departement, UN- Council of Security Declaration.
All these events were every day in media, newspapers, radio, TV.
The Ombudsman could have reacted on the basis of any of these information. In
his competence belongs the right to initiate the alteration of laws refered to
the protection of constitutional and legal rights of citizens. Some of the laws,
enacted by HDZ, were even in collision with the Constitution of Republic of
Croatia, according to the Supreme Court. Mr. Babac has rather stayed hidden and
silent.
Although for his work in last two years was apportioned 1 million DEM from the
State's budget, to this day, he has not appointed his deputies and co-operators.
Therefore the Coordination of Organizations for the Protection and Promotion of
Human Rights of Republic of Croatia, demands the initiative of procedure of
removing Mr. Babac from his office, and more efficacious control of the
Ombudsman's work.<P>

page: 9 - WHAT THE HELL IS SOLICITOR-GENERAL OF RC MARIJAN HRANJSKI WAITING
FOR?(Sto, dodjavola, ceka drzavni odvjetnik RH Marijan Hranjski?)<P>
author: DEJAN KRSIC<P>
In Croatian sensation-mongering press, the misterious report of the three SIS
(Secret Service) agents about the situation in the Ministry of Defense has been
published. The report contains 304 pages of various illegal activities,
buggings, financial malversations, bribes and corruption..etc. There are many
indications that the report was simulated in order to bait and discredit the
opposition. There is also a probability general purge of the old system's
inherited structures, on behalf of the "young lions" of recent war.
The report has not met any reaction of the authorities, nor the legal inquest
of the Solicitor-General, Marijan Hranjski.The whole process has remained only
in the sphere of  sensationalistic media, not in the area of public speech.<P>

page: 10 - THE MAN OF A SPECIAL STAMP (Covjek posebnog kova)<P>
author: BORIS RASETA<P>
A political portrait of Ivica Racan, the chairman of Socialdemocratic party
(of Croatia), former League of Communists.
He always kept the moderate middle line, striking blows left and right, except
in January 1990. in Belgrade, when he has openly opposed. Milosevic  in his
attempt to make Communist party a neo-bolshevist monolith.<P>

page: 11 - A VERTICAL OF NOTHINGNESS(Vertikala nistavila)<P>
author: BOJAN MUNJIN<P>
A deeply moving, meditative report from the devastated Krajina. With a warm,
poetical sensibility the author goes behind the bare statistic of crime into
the realm of the individual tragedy: putting the before the cosmical
reconstruction of the Natural Eros of the past living, on the ashes and traces
of Tanathos, a death-harvest. of "Oluja".A few kilometers from this area of
the medieval havoc., in Zagreb,there is a false, arrogant lustre of the new
state.<P>

page: 12 - THERE IS NO ONE TO SUE THE STATE - (A REGULAR COLUMN :"J'ACCUSE !") (Drzavu nema tko da tuzi)<P>
author: TATJANA TAGIROV<P>
An author considers new alterations of the "Law of the obligatorily relations",
in which there is deleted the duty of state to refund the damage or loss
incured by a terrorist activity. It's only said it would be regulated by the
special ordinances, some day, who knows when. The new law is applicable
retroactively.<P>

page: 12 - TWO REPORTS OF THE NGO: "OPEN EYES"<P>

In Zadar on 27. and 28. february has started a trial against Zvonimir Lasan
(22) for the murder of Janko Sakic, after the military operation "Oluja".
During the trial there was a lot of inconsistency in the statements of wits,
and the defendant.
On which Public prosecutor hasn't reacted with the new questionings. On the
contrary he has proposed to the court to accept the mitigating circumstances,
and Lasan has got only 6 years of prison instead prescribed, at least 10.
In Split on  26 of feb., family Didara was evicted from their flat, all the
property being thrown out on the streets, the woman and man beaten and harassed
by the soldiers. The police didn't protect Didara. They protected the evictors
from the publicity of media and monitoring of NGO's.<P>

page: 13 - A MAN WHO KNOWS TOO MUCH (Covjek koji zna previse)<P>
author: VANESSA VASIC-JANEKOVIC<P>
A confession of the soldier of Army of Bosnian Serbs, Drazen
Erdemovic, who has participated in mass executions of Muslim civilians from
Srebrenica. He describes in details all the massacres of 1200 people on one
field of the farm in Pilice, near Janja, on the road  Bjeljina- Zvornik. The
perpetrators have used the bullets of 7,62 mm, and heavily wounded victims
they've finished off with the coups of Erdemovic didn't want to participate but
was warned that he could be killed too.
After the crime they have excavated the large pit to bury the corpses. Than he
has seen another execution of Muslim people on the street with hand-grenades.
Erdemovic, a child of Serbo-Croatian marriage, was one of many volunteers who
believed in 1991. that he was fighting for Yugoslavia, by besieging Vukovar.
In 1992. in his native Tuzla, first he had joined HVO (Croatian Council of
Defence),than he has run over to the Serbian side. In Serbia he had came in
contact with ABC- TV- station, and has offered his story, and his testimony to
the Haag's Tribunal. Serbian police has arrested him and they will have to
extradite him to the Hague.<P>

page: 14 - WHO SLAUGHTERS WHOM, THERE? (Tko to tamo kolje?)<P>
author: ADA MANDIC<P>
A student from Heidelberg writes about changed situation in Germany, wherein
to be Croat today is exactly like being Serb two years ago. The author wanders
why today  in 1996., and not in 1991 when Croatian reached its very culmination.
It was because of "the affaire Koschnik", she concludes. But the events in
Mostar are only the logical consequence of the same policy that Croats carry on
since the first election in 1990, the policy of ethnically cleansed state.
Fierce Croats in Mostar joggling Koschnik's car, don't seem much worse than
Croats of the first mass-meetings of various Croatian party meetings six years
ago.<P>

page: 14 - BERLIN BANDS FUR BOSNIEN<P>
author: RADIO TTT (DADI)<P>
A benefit concerts of the Berlin groups: Bert'z Rache, C.W. Moss, Time Tough,
Hirn, Ragga Tacke, Auge mit Hering, Posse Connected, Sasha Pushkin, some bands
from Croatia and Bosnia. A 2000 km long tour: Berlin- Pula- Mostar- Tuzla-
-Berlin will start on 15th and 16th of march 1996.,in MILCHHOF (Berlin- Mitte),
than on 31th of march in Pula, Istria, Croatia, than ?? in Mostar on 6th april
in Tuzla, Sportski centar.<P>
Arkzin has also taken part in  organization of this tour.
Web: http:// www. ipn. de/bands
Contact E- mail: Frank.Hofmann@ipn-b.comlink.apc.org<P>

page: 15 - MARVELOUS, WRITE THE MEMOIRS!
            (Idealno, napisite memoare!)<P>
author: ANDREW ROBERTS<P>
After the withdrawal of one barbaric horde, from the mountains and hills
arround Sarajevo, the another ones are coming- tourists. Here is a witty and
ironical guide- leaflet for them.
It offers one: a travel with Maybe Airlines, or bus from Split. In the town: A
ride down Sniper Avenue, the burned University's library, Bascarsija, discarged
bullets and shrapnels....<P>

<a nAME="hdz">page: 15 - JOIN ME TENDERLY (Udruzi me njezno)</a><P>
author: MATO VILAC<P>
The violation of human rights since one year has gradually become legal.
Croatian parliament (Sabor) has enacted series of laws which limit or suspend
the rights and liberties granted by Constitution and previous laws, like
suspending the parts of the Constitutional law of human rights and rights of
national minorities.
"The law of the art and artists", which follows very centralistic legislative
model, favorizes a State arbitration. Even 20 of |{}es were related to the
ministry in authority. The law has many "rubber" articles of the awkward and
polysemantic formulations.
The independent union of professors and scientists, complains that the newly
proposed "Law of  Universities and higher education" proclaims the University's
autonomy, but it doesn't give the mechanism for the implementation of it.
Especially humanisic sciences are thoroughly directed to the state budget, and
state control.
The Coordination of NGO's for the protection and promotion of human rights calls
the public attention to the new "Law of NGO's, associations, and communities",
which establish total control of the State over the work of NGO's, and civic
society, and initiatives.<P>

page: 16 - AN OPEN LETTER TO THE CROATIAN PUBLICITY OF WOMEN'S ORGANIZATION FROM BELGRADE (Otvoreno pismo hrvatskoj javnosti)<P>
Croatian authorities have promised but haven't issued visas for Serbian women's
right activists.<P>

page: 17 - 8th MARCH? HAVEN'T WE RID OF IT?
            (8. mart zar se nismo toga oslobodili?)<P>
author: AIDA BAGIC<P>
The 8th march demonstrations have occured on the "Flower square",in Zagreb, by
distributions of the women rights leaflets and submitting the petition for
women, victims of political systems.<P>

page: 18 - THEY WILL SET IT IN ORDER!
            (One ce to srediti!)<P>
author: IGOR MARKOVIC<P>
In Zagreb in Soros Media Center last weekend, a seminary for women system
operators and e-mail coordinators, was held attending 20 activists. The project
of Djurdja Knezevic, from Zenska Infoteka, Rena Tangens from German Bionica and
Women project APC - guide Sarah Masters.
The project is aiming at participation of more and more women in electronic
communication and raising up generaly the consciousness of women.<P>

page: 19 - WE'VE GOT INTERNET! (IS; IS, HE, HE)
            (Imamo Internet!)<P>
author: DADI (RADIO TTT)<P>
In Croatia there is one Net access, free of charges - CARNET.
It is academic, scientific and non-commercial one. But it gives its service to
everyone and therefore is overloaded. Recently the HPT- the State owned Post and
Telecomunication company, has opened its own Net access, with outrageously
expensive charge. The text deals with a heavy critics of the greed in national
telecom put in a nice and humorous form.<P>

page: 20/21 - I LOVE YOUR PICTURE
               (Sliku tvoju ljubim)<P>
author: TONI GABRIC & MARTINA STAZNIK<P>
Four months after the elections on which HDZ has won again and again has turn
a relative majority in an absolute power, the same pre-election jumbo- poster of
president Tudjman hanged on several places. This time in Zagreb's city council
HDZ has got 17 seats and opposition 33. Nevertheless HDZ again wants absolute
power.
But this is not important. What is important is the head on the jumbo posters,
the only constant value in last 6 years. It has installed 5 prime ministers and
governments, ministries judges, mayors, even sport couches. He has given his
statements about miss-concourses, pop-music...
For the sake of his own historical magnitude he has lightly acceded the war,
and sent thousands of young people in death.
A brief public inquiry shows that many citizens don't like the poster. It
reminds them  of Soviet, Chinese or Korean communism.<P>

page: 22 - ARKZIN also brings the letters of reactions of journalist Drago
Pilsel, and the executive director of HHO (Croatian Helsinky Committee),
Petar Mrkalj, on the article "Shame", about visit to a refugee
camp, Gasinci, from the issue 59, written by Igor Markovic.<P>

page: 22 - A CERTIFICATE ONLY ON THE NEXT ELECTIONS
            (Diploma tek na slijedecim izborima)<P>
author: IVAN STAGLICIC<P>

As the reaction on the government's intention to build a giant termo-power
plant in Obrovac, that would certainly change the microclimate negatively, in
the area of the well-developed tourism, and subterraneous waters, the
oppositional parties in Zadar were actuated to establish a Coordination board
to cope with such a policy. The petition against this project have signed, so
far,15 780 citizens.<P>

page: 23 - LEA-DER-LEAD-ER-LE-ADER-LE-ADER
            (Vo-dja-vo-dja-vo-dja-vo-dja)<P>
author: DEJAN JOVIC<P>
An author is on the postdoctoral studies in London. He refers to the lecture
given by Bosnian ambassador, Muhamed Filipovic, wherein he regarded Nikola
Koljevic, the right-hand-man (after Biljana Plavsic) of Radovan
Karadzic, the leader of Bosnian Serbs, originally as Bulgarian.
Filipovic's ancestors were Croats, Karadzic is Montenegrin, and
Mladic - Serbian.
After Filipovic came Novak Kilibarda, a leader of Montenegrin pro- Serbian
opposition. He was full of praises for Tudjman and his leadership of Croatian
people.
Jovic than extended to the year 1954. when in Buenos Aires, Argentina, have met
Croatian ex-fuhrer (Poglavnik) Ante Pavelic, and Serbian fuehrer (Vodja) Milan
Stojadinovic.
They've made the appointement to overthrow Tito's regime and split Yugoslavia
assunder, on Croatia and Serbia; exchanging people and territories, in order to
fix the borders between them. (Sounds familiar?) Pavelic said Bosnia and
Herzegovina was an artificial product of the occupation made by Turkish Empire,
and should be divided in two. (Sounds familiar?)<P>

page: 24 - STINGIES DON'T LOVE - (LOVE & BALKANS)
            (Skrti, ne ljube)<P>
author: SLAVICA MANDIC<P>

"For a true love it is not important how much money man sacrifices to his female
partner, but wether he gives all of his posession or just a part of it."<P>

page: 24/25 - FOR THE GROWING GENERATION
               (Za generaciju koja raste)<P>
author: IGOR MARKOVIC<P>
A long expected magazin for the culture of youth: Homo Volans is like a house
of pared claes, brought to the exhibition of pets, even winning a prize. A
peaceful, tame, aesthetic, something to be a proud of. "Nevertheless", Markovic
says, "I prefer a stray Tom-cat which takes care of himself, chasing mice and
rats and winning the favour of a she-cat, not waiting that someone choose him a
match."  The magazine is an ivory tower of pompous self-sufficiency, of
frivolous reviews in the same style: cold, aloof, skilfully written, but
without a personal eros in it.<P>

page: 25 - STUDENTS MOVE ON
            (Studenti krecu)<P>
author: ROBERT VALKAJ<P>
A Coordination of Students Associations of Zagreb, has been established in
order to protect the rights and interests of students.
They want: a) a new law of students to solve clearly the issue of student
organizations and sphere of activity of them.b) participation of student
representatives in all the Universty's institutions, Students Center (SC),etc.<P>

<a NAME="body">page: 26 - BODY IS (NOT) A PRIVILEGE OF LIFE
            (Tijelo (ni)je privilegij zivota)</a><P>
author IGOR MARKOVIC<P>

Marcel-Li Antunez a Mexican body-artist, has recently made a performance in
ZKM (Zagreb's theater of youngs), named Epizoo, or epidemic of animals, a
bastard of performance and installation, adopted to the new computer techniques.
It consists of a set of pneumatic mechanisms affixed on two metal shuttles,
attached on his back. Thus enables the movements of various parts of body; ears,
nose, ass, chest. On the screen behind is 2D and 3D animation. The author
produces onomatopoeic sounds on a microphone. The project shows a basic desire
to rebuild a man in new civilization of Mind.<P>

page: 27 -  ONE NEEDS TO EXPERIMENT!
             (Treba eksperimentirati!)<P>
author: VESNA JANKOVIC & IGOR MARKOVIC<P>

An interview with Marcel-Li Antunez. He considers his own approach to body-art
as more theatrical and interactive than Stelarc's (see the issue 49.). He would
like to work with servomotors that bring more control and possibilities thab
with pneumatic, but he is too short in funds.
The exhibitions in Ljubljana and Podgorica were interesting: severed heads,
pleasure-machines, love letters....It's like architecture, one has a space to
fill up.
"I am a hedonist, I love the life, my body and other bodies. For me, Eros means
food, sunshine, relation of me and the nature. I am a sort of pantheist. The
technology is only a means, a tool, not the idea of performance.<P>

page: 28 - SQUADRA DOESN'T WANT DIMITRIJE!
            (Nece skvadra Dimitrija!)<P>
author: MARTINA STAZNIK<P>

"The prejudice has always followed tattooing as a symbol of outcasts and
losers or symbol of sex, nature and freedom. In a course of time it has turned
into a legitimated form of art. Standards have advanced, the educated artists
have introduced studious paintings, and removed tattooing from the dark streets,
amateur pictures and frivolous inscriptions.."
"Roby's tattoo shop",in Zagreb, has been opened since 1992. The prices run from
40 DEM up. Catalogues are full of agressive, destructive drawings. Just like a
time.<P>

page: 29 - MICRO RADIO STATIONS, AS SUCH, AND WIDER...
            (Radio stanice, kao takve, a i sire)<P>
author: RADIO-TTT_ZG@ZAMIR-ZG.ZTN.APC.ORG<P>

The idea of "free radio" was a programme of those included in social changes
since the beginning of radio broadcasting. During 2nd world war, Algerian war
and national liberation wars, free radio was an important weapon, but first
mini FM has appeared in 70's in Italy due to Felix Guattary, who has very
creatively connected political ideas with the sub-cultural endeavours towards
idea of free radio stations.
The boom was fantastic. In Europe, America, Japan. It has become a global
movement, very often cursed and persecuted by the Establishment, as "home
enemies", "foreign hirelings", "obnoxious".
In Croatia there were many examples of pirate (mini FM) radio stations: Radio
Slic, Radio Lucifer, Radio Utopija, Radio Susjedi jel'me cujete; Radio Dugave,
Radio Gajnice.
But they have died off.<P>

page: 29 - I HAVE DREAMED TONIGHT...
            (Sanjao sam nocas...)<P>
author: IGOR MARKOVIC<P>
Bill Viola, the American video-artist, National Endowment for Art Laureate,
has installed his exhibition; "The Passing" from 1991. in Multimedial center
(MM), in Zagreb. The Passing considers a dualistic nature of dream and reality,
time and space. A relativity of life, passing from one state in other is
represented all 70 minutes of black and white pictures on a screen,in which are
used the interieurs of hospitals and flats, the exterieurs of Californian bays,
water, Death valley, tunnels, highways, but all as if caught in an eyes angle,
on the edge of a vague dreamland.<P>

page: 30/31 - MOVIE REVIEWS OF:<P>

- SEX SA STRANCEM - THE BRIDGES OF MADISON COUNTY
