<HEAD>
<TITLE>Nenad</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<FONT SIZE="+1">

<center><h1>Nenad, 13</h1></center>
<em>December 1994<br>
Bileca, Bosnia-Hercegovina</em><P>

<IMG SRC="http://www.sailing.org/Yugoslavia/peopref4.gif" ALT="Nenad's picture" HIGHT=294 WIDTH=288><P><hr><P>

Nenad was lazily watching TV one afternoon in Capljina when his life ubruptly changed: his parents shouted that they had five minutes to leave their town and home.  "It was a big rush," recalled Nenad simply, adding that his family took only a large bag filled with clothes.  That was almost three years ago.  Nenad, an older brother, and a 2-month-old sister now live with seven other relatives in a deserted house in Bileca.  School is OK, Nenad says shyly, but what he dreams of is to be a car mechanic.<P>

