<HEAD>
<TITLE> Vukovar, Srbi 2</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<FONT SIZE="+1">
<hr>

<IMG SRC="/info/students/marko/pictures/vukovar6.gif"><P>

The corpse of a man wearing a police uniform was found in the Danube near Susek.  The man was killed with a sharp object - most probably a knife.  The corpse was identified as that of Milorad Dekic, the son of Novo and Persa.  He was a policeman in the Osijek Police Department, where he has worked for 14 years.  His wife Spomenka also had a job in the Osijek Police Department. Milorad Dekic was born on October 12 1957 in the village of Cecava in the municipality of Teslic, Bosnia and Hercegovina.<P>

The corpse of a man was found in the Danube near Bolec on July 17 1991.  the corpse was identified as that of Milenko Duricic, a Serb born on June 18 1953 to father Ilija and mother Tonka; he was married and father of a child.  He was an employee of "Borovo" Works.<br>
The corpse was wrapped in a woolen blanket; nooses with tight knots tied his neck and ankles.  The nooses were interconnected by a rope slung over the back.  the arms and legs were also tied.  It was determined that several teeth had been knocked out, sternum was fractured as well as 6th, 7th, 8th, 9th, 10th and 11th ribs.  Death was by drowning.<P>

<IMG SRC="/info/students/marko/pictures/vukovar4.gif"><P>
The corpse of a man whose legs were tied and hands handcuffed was wound on October 27 1991 on the shore of "Ljubavno Ostrvo" (an island on the Danube river, near Futog).  Death was caused by firearm wounds.  The corpse was identified as that of Bozo Skoric, a Serb born on January 8 1952 in Vukovar, to Mico and Manda Skoric.  He lived at 16 S. Marinkovica St. in Vukovar.<P>

<IMG SRC="/info/students/marko/pictures/vukovar4a.gif"><P>
Bozo Skoric's identity card<P>

The corpse of Zdravko Dadic was found in the Danube, near Sremska Kamenica, opposite the "Ilidza" restaurant, on October 17 1991.  He was born in 1949 and lived at 24 Otokara Kersovanija St., Marinci, municipality of Vukovar. Zdravko Dadic's identity card, driver's license and a union card were found in his pockets.<P></FONT>

