<TITLE>refpic7</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="pictures/frback.jpg">

<HR>
<IMG SRC="pictures/refpic7.gif" WIDTH=340 HEIGHT=490 ALIGN="RIGHT" BORDER=1>
<P>

<STRONG><FONT SIZE="+2"> They shot at us on the way.  I thought that our [soldiers] were carrying ammunition and guns in those trucks.  They hit the trucks and both trucks and 3 small automobiles burst into flames.  Both trucks and cars burned to ashes.  Nine persons died, men, women and children.  This happened on Sunday near Bosanski Petrovac [a town in western Bosnia].  And trucks were full of cans, to feed the refugees...<P>

I didn't think that I would flee my own house and that I would cry the whole way;  I haven't seen my child since Friday.  He's been on the front for five years.  He's been defending Krajina but he hasn't saved it.  let God punish those who did this to me.  We are now in a foreign land.  I don't have anyone here, nowhere to go, nowhere to sleep... </FONT></STRONG>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="+1">Novi Sad, FR Yugoslavia (Serbia-Montenegro), August 1995<BR>
<BR><I>&copy; 1995, Gordana Todorov</I></FONT>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE="+2>
<H2>Fighting stops to let refugees flee under U.N. escort</H2>
<H4>(c) 1995 Copyright the News & Observer Publishing Co.<P>
 (c) 1995 Associated Press</A></H4>
 
   ZAGREB, Croatia (Aug 9, 1995 - 12:01 EDT) --Thousands of exhausted, frightened Serb refugees fled east toward the Yugoslav border Wednesday after Croatia promised not to attack them. Croat civilians gathered by the side of the road to curse them as they left.<P>

   "Go faster," elderly Croats shouted at the line of cars, many of which had bicycles on top. "You monkeys," others cursed.<P>
......<P>

   LePage said the United Nations also was investigating the possible bombing of civilians Tuesday near Dvor.<P>

   She said two MiG-21s dropped four bombs on unknown targets. Minutes earlier, two MiG-21s, laden with weapons, had been seen leaving Zagreb airport in the direction of Dvor.<P>

   Gen. Zvonimir Cervenko, the Croatian army commander, denied that Croatian jets were attacking civilians. However, he said, "it was possible that some civilians were killed" in attacks on other targets. He charged Serb forces had used civilians near Dvor as a cover while they withdrew heavy weapons.<P>

