<STRONG><FONT SIZE="+2"> We crossed 1000km with a small baby.  She [the baby] has a fever, 39C.  There's no more accommodations for the mother and the child.  I don't know what we are going to do...  We've been here [in the car] for 3 days.  The mother has gone to try to find some food for the baby, it's hard for children...  I am a refugee from Krajina...  I have nothing else to say.</FONT>  </STRONG>
<P>

<FONT SIZE="+1">Novi Sad, FR Yugoslavia (Serbia-Montenegro), August 1995<BR>
