<TITLE>Croatian Foreign Minister meets US Assistant Secretary of State</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

used without permission, for "fair use" only<hr>
<FONT SIZE="+1">
 

<h1>IMPORTANT STEPS IN IMPLEMENTATION OF THE AGREEMENT</h1>

<strong><em>by Marinko Boboanovic</em></strong><P>

<h2>Vjesnik, Zagreb, Croatia, 05/23/96</h2>


Zagreb, 22 May. " We are satisfied with the fact that the
elections shall be held in Mostar as envisaged or at least
within the envisaged time frame. The talks regarding placing
controls on weaponry shall soon be concluded and the
decision regarding general elections is also expected soon.
This is one on the vital steps in the implementation of the
Dayton agreements and also one of the steps towards the
resolution of the problem of Bosnia Herzegovina," said the
Assistant Secretary of State of the United States for
European and Canadian Affairs, Mr John Kornblum, following
his talks with the President of the Republic of Croatia, Dr
Franjo Tudman. The visit of Secretary Kornblum to Zagreb,
and prior to that to Belgrade, according to his words, arose
because of the development on new events including the
unclear political situation in the "Republika Srpska".<P>

This is, according to Kornblum "in fact only one in a series
of visits for the purpose of which is the implementation of
the Dayton agreements, setting up a dialogue process, the
identification of problems and their joint resolution, prior
to there becoming crises," said Kornblem. He repeated the
United States' commitment to the implementation of the
Dayton agreements. In particular he emphasised the
importance that all sides fulfil their obligations so that
"all sides can make use of the advantages that the
Agreements bring".<P>

According to the Croatian Minister for Foreign Affairs  Dr
Mate Granic, who participated in the talks between President
Tudman and Secretary Kornblum mentioned also the
implementation of the agreement regarding the peaceful
reintegration of eastern Slavonija and generally Croatian-
American relations. "The joint conclusion was that the
process of the peaceful reintegration of eastern Slavonija
is progressing well and that it will be a success", said Dr
Granic.<P>

"Mr Kornblum informed us of all steps being taken by the US
Administration to resolve the unclear situation with the
"Republika Srpska" and Karadzic," added Dr Granic. He
emphasised that the United States and Croatia are making
joint efforts to strengthen the Federation and that the most
recent step related to that was taken in Washington at the
Federation Forum which had very concrete results.<P>

Dr Granic announced that an American business delegation
headed by Assistant Secretary Mr Kantor shall soon visit
Croatia and added that another important delegation is
already in Croatia. The conclusion was that relations
between the two countries are "developing well and are on an
ascending course" said Dr Granic.<P>
<center>
                              ~
</center>
