<H4><b>Clas A. Jacobson</H4></b> <BR><b>Associate Professor</b> <BR><P>Office: 413 Dana Building <BR>tel:617-373-5653, fax:617-373-4189 <BR>jacobson@cdsp.neu.edu <BR>
<P>
<P>Professor Jacobson received the BS  degree
in Computer and Systems Engineering in 1982, and the MEng and PhD
degrees in Electrical Engineering in 1984 and 1986, respectively,
from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, Troy, New York.
<P>
 Dr. Jacobson
has active research interests in the control of distributed parameter
systems, failure detection and isolation for dynamic systems and
control oriented system identification. His application interests include
the active control of airborne acoustic noise, the control of
switched reluctance machines and control problems in power systems including
the design of power system stabilizers and the control of FACTS devices.
<P>
<P><b>Selected Publications</b>
<P>
<P>An Integrated
Approach to Controls and Diagnostics: The 4-Parameter Controller. 
 C.N. Nett and C.A. Jacobson,  
<i>IEEE Control Systems Magazine</i>, <i>22-29</i>, Oct. 1991.
<P>
<P>Identification in
<IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../tadmor/h_inf.gif">: The Continuous Time Case.  A.J. Helmicki, C.A. Jacobson, 
and C.N. Nett,   <i>IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control</i>, April 1992.
<P>
<P>On Zero Order
Equivalents of Distributed Parameter Systems.   C.A. Helmicki, C.A.
Jacobson, and C.N. Nett,  <i>IEEE
Transactions on Automatic Control</i>, April 1992.
<P>
<P>Identification in <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="../tadmor/h_inf.gif">: A Robustly Convergent Nonlinear
Algorithm. A. J. Helmicki, C.A. Jacobson, and C. N. Nett, 
<i>IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control</i>, Oct. 1991.
<P>
<P>Ill Posed Distributed Parameter Systems: A Control
Viewpoint.  A. J. Helmicki, C.A. Jacobson,  and C. N. Nett,  <i>IEEE
Transactions on Automatic Control</i>, Sept. 1991.
<P>
<P>Linear State-Space Systems in
Infinite-Dimensional Space: The Role and Characterization of Joint
Stabilizability &amp; Detectability.  C.A. Jacobson and C.N. Nett,   <i>IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control</i>, <b>AC-33</b>,
<i>541-549</i>, June 1988.
<P>

