<h1><BR>NORTHEASTERN UNIVERSITY<BR> HUSKY HOCKEY </h1>

<hr align="right" width="100%">
<BR CLEAR="left">

Welcome to the Unofficial Northeastern University Husky Hockey homepage.
This page was created and is maintained by a graduate student hockey fan.
Please mail any comments or suggestions to: 
<i><a href ="mailto:liz@cdsp.neu.edu"> liz@cdsp.neu.edu</a></i> 
<p>
<hr align="right" width="100%">
<font color="black"><b>NOTE to any NU students who read this:</b></font>  I'm thinking about going out to UMass for the game on the 17th.  That's my alma mater and I like to go back for this game.  If anyone is interested in coming along, email me...<BR>

<hr align="right" width="100%">


<img src="he.gif"><BR>
Men's Head Coach:   Bruce Crowder<BR>
Asst. Coaches:  Mark Carlson, Paul Cannata, Ed Arrington<BR>
<p>
<img src="ecac.gif"><BR>
Women's Head Coach:  Heather Lindstad<BR>
Asst. Coach:  Rayanne Conway<BR>
Goalie Coach:  Michelle DiSteffano<BR>
<p>
Home Ice: Matthews Arena, St. Botolph Street, Boston MA 
 

<p>
<hr align="right" width="100%">
<p> 
<font color="black"><b>CURRENT WEEKEND (1/9-1/12):</b></font><BR>
<dd>The men had their first home game in way too long on Thursday vs. the Friars of Providence College.  The Huskies took an lead 1-0 in the first period, but the Friars answered with 5 demoralizing goals.  NU came back to bring it within 1, but just couldn't tie it.  Final score 5-4, Providence.  Congratulations to <b>Todd Barclay</b> on his very nice hat trick.<BR>

<dd>On Saturday, they traveled across town to the infamous Walter Brown Arena to face Boston University.  My trusty hockey fan friend and I also ventured out, along with maybe 5 other NU fans and were rewarded with a pretty good game, even though the Huskies lost 5-4.  BU never went up more than one goal, and the teams were tied until 9 minutes left.<BR>
<p>
Congratulations to <b>Marc Robitaille</b> on being named Hockey East Rookie of the Week, the only goalie to earn this so far this year.  We're big fans.<BR>
<p>
<li><a href = "http://www.nunews.neu.edu/current/011597s5.htm">"Men's hockey falls one short ... twice"</a>  (from January 15 issue <i>NU News</i>)<BR>

<p>
<dd>The women had two home games:  A 4-0 win on Saturday vs. St. Lawrence, and a 2-1 loss on Sunday against Cornell.<BR>
<li><a href = "http://www.nunews.neu.edu/current/011597s3.htm">"Huskies not knee-ling to foes"</a>  (from January 15 issue <i>NU News</i>)<BR>

<p>

<font color="black"><b>NEXT WEEKEND: (1/17-1/20)</b></font><BR>
<dd>The women have three games in at the Providence Tournament:  Thursday vs. Providence, Friday vs. UNH, and Saturday vs. Concordia.
<p>
<dd>The men have a home-and-home series with UMass, Friday in Amherst and Saturday at NU.

