</DOCHDR>
Scalar and vector Kalman filters are implemented for filtering speech 
contaminated by additive white or colored noise and an iterative signal 
and parameter estimator which can be used for both noise types is 
presented.  Particular emphasis is placed on the removal of colored noise,  
such as helicopter noise, by using state-of-the-art colored noise assumption 
Kalman filters.  The results indicate that the colored noise Kalman filters 
provide a significant gain in the SNR, a visible improvement in the sound  
spectrogram, and an audible improvement in the output speech quality, none 
of which are available with the white noise assumption Kalman and Wiener 
filters.  When the filter is employed as a prefilter for linear predictive 
coding, the coded output speech quality and intelligibility is greatly 
enhanced in comparison to direct coding of the noisy speech.    
</DOC>
