</DOCHDR>
We propose and study a new technique for estimating the weight of very heavy 
objects.  This new technique is based on measurements made by a device, 
a gravity 
gradiometer, that is capable of measuring subtle changes in the gravitational 
field produced by an object with respect to distance.  
The physical observables, 
known as gravity gradients, depend upon the mass density distribution 
of an object 
and the relative distance between the object and the measurement device.  
We show that for very heavy objects gravity gradient measurements 
can be used to make accurate weight 
estimates.   This technology could be potentially 
important in the eventual implementation 
of arms control agreements or for application in the transportation industry.

</DOC>
